def create_charts(df):
    import plotly.graph_objects as go
    from plotly.subplots import make_subplots
    
    # Sort the dataframe by readmission_rate
    df_sorted = df.sort_values(by='readmission_rate', ascending=True)
    
    # Create the first figure: Bar chart for readmission rate
    fig1 = go.Figure()
    fig1.add_trace(go.Bar(
        x=df_sorted['time_in_hospital'],
        y=df_sorted['readmission_rate'],
        marker_color='#44BFFC',
        name='Readmission Rate'
    ))
    fig1.update_layout(
        title='Readmission Rate by Time in Hospital',
        xaxis_title='Time in Hospital (days)',
        yaxis_title='Readmission Rate',
        template='plotly_white'
    )
    
    # Create the second figure: Scatter plot for average length of stay vs readmission rate
    fig2 = make_subplots(rows=1, cols=1)
    fig2.add_trace(go.Scatter(
        x=df_sorted['average_length_of_stay'],
        y=df_sorted['readmission_rate'],
        mode='markers',
        marker=dict(color='#81FBA5'),
        name='Avg Length of Stay vs Readmission Rate'
    ))
    fig2.update_layout(
        title='Average Length of Stay vs Readmission Rate',
        xaxis_title='Average Length of Stay (days)',
        yaxis_title='Readmission Rate',
        template='plotly_white'
    )
    
    return {
        "fig1": fig1,
        "fig2": fig2
    }
